{"HERMA":[{"def":"Defn: See Hermes, 2.","pos":""}],"HERMAPHRODEITY":[{"def":"Her*maph`ro*de\"i*ty, n.","pos":""}],"HERMAPHRODISM":[{"def":"See Hermaphroditism.","pos":""}],"HERMAPHRODITE":[{"def":"An individual which has the attributes of both male and female, or which unites in itself the two sexes; an animal or plant having the parts of generation of both sexes, as when a flower contains both the stamens and pistil within the same calyx, or on the same receptacle.","pos":""}],"HERMAPHRODITISM":[{"def":"The union of the two sexes in the same individual, or the combination of some of their characteristics or organs in one individual.","pos":""},{"def":"Unfolding the signification; of or pertaining to interpretation; exegetical; explanatory; as, hermeneutic theology, or the art of expounding the Scriptures; a hermeneutic phrase.","pos":""}],"HERMENEUTICALLY":[{"def":"According to the principles of interpretation; as, a verse of Scripture was examined hermeneutically.","pos":""}],"HERMENEUTICS":[{"def":"The science of interpretation and explanation; exegesis; esp.","pos":""}],"HERMES":[{"def":"Of, pertaining to, or taught by, Hermes Trismegistus; as, hermetic philosophy.","pos":""},{"def":"Of or pertaining to the system which explains the causes of diseases and the operations of medicine on the principles of the hermetic philosophy, and which made much use, as a remedy, of an alkali and an acid; as, hermetic medicine.","pos":""}],"HERMETICALLY":[{"def":"In an hermetical manner; chemically.","pos":""},{"def":"By fusion, so as to form an air-tight closure.","pos":""}],"HERMIT":[{"def":"A person who retires from society and lives in solitude; a recluse; an anchoret; especially, one who so lives from religious motives.","pos":""},{"def":"A beadsman; one bound to pray for another.","pos":""}],"HERMITAGE":[{"def":"A celebrated French wine, both white and red, of the Department of Drôme.","pos":""}],"HERMITARY":[{"def":"A cell annexed to an abbey, for the use of a hermit.","pos":""}],"HERMITESS":[{"def":"A female hermit.","pos":""}],"HERMITICAL":[{"def":"Pertaining to, or suited for, a hermit.","pos":""}],"HERMODACTYL":[{"def":"A heart-shaped bulbous root, about the size of a finger, brought from Turkey, formerly used as a cathartic.","pos":""}],"HERMOGENIAN":[{"def":"A disciple of Hermogenes, and heretical teacher who lived in Africa near the close of the second century.","pos":""}]}